# ProjectFlo — API Design

- All backend routes live under `/api/*`.
- Prefer nested resources when the child is always accessed via a parent (e.g. `/api/inquiries/:inquiryId/estimates`).
- For state-changing actions beyond CRUD, use `POST` with a verb suffix (`/send`, `/refresh`, `/revise`); never use `GET` for mutations.
- Parse numeric path params with `ParseIntPipe`.
- Apply `@UseGuards(AuthGuard('jwt'))` at the controller level (not per-route).
- Validate inputs with `ValidationPipe` on `@Body()` / `@Query()`.
- Responses:
  - single-resource: return the entity (no wrapper)
  - list: return an array
  - mutations: may return `{ id, status }` if full entity is expensive
- Errors: keep NestJS default exception response shape; don’t override it.
- Naming: controller/service methods follow `findAll`, `findOne`, `create`, `update`, `remove`, and action verbs for action endpoints.

